Do we know if the class is going to be webcasted yet?

history.content:
Hi all, EECS C106A is expanding.

We've currently added 20 seats and plan to add another 20 at the start of the semester, bringing the total capacity to 180 students (though some seats are still reserved for graduate and exchange students). We're already going to be stretched to the limit on hardware availability, so we will not expand the course again. Note that it might take a day or two for the new lab sections to show up.

Regarding attendance, you're required to attend the lab section in which you're enrolled. While there will be a mechanism to switch lab sections once the semester begins, do not plan on being able to switch. You will be dropped from the class if you cannot attend your assigned lab section.

You may attend any discussion section, but if room capacity is exceeded, students enrolled in that section will be prioritized.

Feel free to ask any questions below.

- Valmik
